# Global Standards

## Pipeline Initialization (CRITICAL)

- **Any task MUST begin by initializing the protocol defined in `agent-pipeline.mdc`.**
- The pipeline (Priority 100) orchestrates all phases: Discovery → Simulation → TDD Execution → Verification → Brain Sync → Confidence.
- Domain standards live in their respective rules. The pipeline enforces them — never bypass it.

## 0.1 Conditional Rule Routing (CRITICAL)

Do NOT assume Cursor auto-attaches glob-scoped rules. `alwaysApply: false` rules attach inconsistently, so before planning/editing in a task area, **explicitly read the matching conditional rules**:

- **React / component / hook / page / HOC work** → `react-patterns.mdc`, `engineering-standards.mdc`, `performance.mdc`
- **New behavioral component or changed behavior** → also `test-driven-development.mdc` before implementation
- **Tests / specs / fixtures / mocks** → `test-driven-development.mdc`
- **API client / TanStack Query / data-fetching / payload contracts** → `api.mdc`, `resilience.mdc`, `engineering-standards.mdc`
- **Zustand stores / selectors / server-state** → `state-management.mdc`, `resilience.mdc`, `engineering-standards.mdc`
- **Router / route organization / pages** → `routing.mdc`
- **Async / error handling / debugging** → `resilience.mdc`
- **Styling / render-perf / memo / list keys** → `performance.mdc` + `react-patterns.mdc`
- **Constants / magic strings / config values** → `constants.mdc`, `engineering-standards.mdc`
- **PWA / service worker / `vite.config.ts` / manifest / `index.html` meta / MSW** → `project-config.mdc` §PWA + **mandatory** `.cursor/brain/PWA.md` + `.cursor/brain/SKELETONS.md` (load-bearing, destructive-to-change config)

Always-on rules (`agent-pipeline.mdc`, `global.mdc`, `workflow.mdc`, `project-config.mdc`) attach automatically — they need not appear in the Rule Receipt (`agent-pipeline.mdc` Phase 1).

## Language (chat vs codebase)

- **Chat with the user:** Russian by default unless the user switches language.
- **New agent/session default:** First and all subsequent chat replies must be in Russian unless the user explicitly requests another language.
- **Codebase:** English only — source, identifiers, comments, JSDoc, tests, and Git messages (`type(scope): subject`). Brain/docs under `.cursor/brain/` may be English for template consistency; do not mix Russian into production code or commits.

## Intelligence & Context

- **Reasoning**: Use `sequential-thinking` (if available in your environment) for logic and `context7` for docs lookups.
- **Authority**: `.cursor/brain/` (MAP, DECISIONS, SKELETONS, DICTIONARY) is the Source of Truth. Sync drifts immediately.
- **Stack**: Strict **TypeScript**. React 19. Prioritize existing libs over custom logic.
- **Quality**: Minimalist code. No magic strings — use constants or i18n keys.
- **Clean Code**: Descriptive naming, performance-oriented. Explain complex logic with single-line `//` only.
- **Hygiene**: Keep AI metadata and agent-only specs in `.cursor/`. Normal project docs like `README.md` or deployment checklists may live in root when they are part of the template contract.
- **Git**: `type(scope): description` — English, max 96 chars. No "Co-authored-by" tags.
